==============================================================================
COMMERCIAL USE FAQ (non-binding, for clarity)
==============================================================================
The distinction below reflects how we intend to interpret Section 2
("COMMERCIAL USE REQUIRES A PAID LICENSE") in good faith. The license
text itself controls in the event of conflict.

Q: I'm a freelancer / solo developer using it to automate MY OWN work.
A: FREE. You are not redistributing the Software and you are not
   offering it as a service to anyone else. Use it, modify it, keep
   your changes private — no license needed.

Q: I'm an agency / consultancy. I use it internally to build and run
   an automation FOR a specific client, as part of the service my
   agency sells to that client.
A: FREE, as long as:
     - the Software (or a derivative) is not delivered to the client
       as a standalone product they can run without you;
     - the client is not charged specifically for access to the
       Software or a Software-as-a-Service tier built on it;
     - the Software remains running on your or the client's own
       infrastructure under a one-to-one relationship.
   This is treated as "internal tooling of the agency serving its
   client" under Section 1(b).

Q: I re-brand it, wrap it with my own UI, and charge end-users a
   monthly subscription to use it.
A: NEEDS A COMMERCIAL LICENSE. This is resale / paid SaaS under
   Section 2(a)-(c).

Q: I host it on a VPS and let ONE paying customer log in and use it.
A: NEEDS A COMMERCIAL LICENSE. "One paying customer" is still
   "offering the Software as a hosted service for a paying user"
   under Section 2(c). Number of users is not the test — whether
   anyone is paying for access is.

Q: My company uses it internally for our own employees to automate
   their tasks. No external customers touch it. No one pays to use it.
A: FREE under Section 1(b) (internal, non-revenue-generating
   organisational use).

Q: I build an internal tool that uses it behind the scenes and
   generates revenue indirectly (e.g., a bot that helps our sales
   team prospect).
A: FREE, as long as the Software itself is not sold, sublicensed, or
   exposed as a paid product or paid API to anyone outside the
   organisation.

Q: I want to fork it, add features, and share the fork publicly on
   GitHub for free.
A: FREE under Section 1(c), as long as (i) you release the fork under
   this same license, (ii) you keep the copyright notice and
   attribution, and (iii) you do not charge for access to the fork.

Q: I want to train an AI / benchmark / agent-eval on data produced
   or collected by this Software.
A: NEEDS A SEPARATE WRITTEN LICENSE. See Section 3(e). This applies
   even if your downstream use is non-commercial.

Q: I'm unsure which category I fall into.
A: Email admin@32d.one with a short description of your use case.
   We answer quickly and most "unsure" cases turn out to be FREE.
   Commercial pricing, when applicable, scales with the size of the
   deployment (seats, end-users, or revenue of the offering), and
   starts well below the cost of rebuilding the Software from
   scratch.
